    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 10,
        "summary": "A wise son makes a glad father\u2014The mouth of a righteous man is a well of life\u2014He who utters slander is a fool\u2014The desire of the righteous will be granted.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The proverbs of Solomon. A wise son maketh a glad father: but a foolish son is the heaviness of his mother.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 4:32; Prov. 1:1; 25:1.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 17:21.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Happiness.",
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Fatherhood.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 15:5, 20.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0sorrow.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 92
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Children, Duties of; Marriage, Motherhood.",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Treasures of wickedness profit nothing: but righteousness delivereth from death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The Lord will not suffer the soul of the righteous to famish: but he casteth away the substance of the wicked.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He becometh poor that dealeth with a slack hand: but the hand of the diligent maketh rich.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Laziness.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Dedication; Diligence.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that gathereth in summer is a wise son: but he that sleepeth in harvest is a son that causeth shame.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 46
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Blessings are upon the head of the just: but violence covereth the mouth of the wicked.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 39:8.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 9
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The memory of the just is blessed: but the name of the wicked shall rot.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wickedness.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 14:22; Jer. 51:62 (61\u201362).",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The wise in heart will receive commandments: but a prating fool shall fall.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that walketh uprightly walketh surely: but he that perverteth his ways shall be known.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 28:6.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that winketh with the eye causeth sorrow: but a prating fool shall fall.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The mouth of a righteous man is a well of life: but violence covereth the mouth of the wicked.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 37:30; Alma 36:26; D&C 108:7.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 13:14.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Hatred stirreth up strifes: but love covereth all sins.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hate; Malice.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contention.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In the lips of him that hath understanding wisdom is found: but a rod is for the back of him that is void of understanding.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:29.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Wise men lay up knowledge: but the mouth of the foolish is near destruction.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 18:7.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The rich man's wealth is his strong city: the destruction of the poor is their poverty.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 18:11.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The labour of the righteous tendeth to life: the fruit of the wicked to sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Labor; Work, Value of.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:23.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He is in the way of life that keepeth instruction: but he that refuseth reproof erreth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Teachable.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 49
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastening; Reproof.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that hideth hatred with lying lips, and he that uttereth a slander, is a fool.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hate.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Slander.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In the multitude of words there wanteth not sin: but he that refraineth his lips is wise.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Boast.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 17:27.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The tongue of the just is as choice silver: the heart of the wicked is little worth.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The lips of the righteous feed many: but fools die for want of wisdom.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 14:1 (1\u20137).",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The blessing of the Lord, it maketh rich, and he addeth no sorrow with it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Treasure.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "It is as sport to a fool to do mischief: but a man of understanding hath wisdom.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The fear of the wicked, it shall come upon him: but the desire of the righteous shall be granted.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As the whirlwind passeth, so is the wicked no more: but the righteous is an everlasting foundation.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As vinegar to the teeth, and as smoke to the eyes, so is the sluggard to them that send him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The fear of the Lord prolongeth days: but the years of the wicked shall be shortened.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reverence.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The hope of the righteous shall be gladness: but the expectation of the wicked shall perish.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hope.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The way of the Lord is strength to the upright: but destruction shall be to the workers of iniquity.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strength.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The righteous shall never be removed: but the wicked shall not inhabit the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 2:21 (21\u201322).",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 1:8.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The mouth of the just bringeth forth wisdom: but the froward tongue shall be cut out.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0perverse.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable: but the mouth of the wicked speaketh frowardness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 10:12.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}